The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, June 03, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, June 3, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Stretch in front of Coal India HQ at BBD Bag. Citu demonstration at 1 pm.				 																Soccer meet				 																																	Semi-final matches of The Telegraph Merchants Cup Football Tournament, organised by CC amp;FC, on the club grounds, 7.30 pm onwards.				 																Earth talk				 																																	An adda on environmental issues, organised by American Center, aboard a launch of Calcutta Port Trust, at 4 pm. An award-winning film will also be screened. 				 																Music				 																																	An interactive music session with rock band Krosswindz for children at Crossword Bookstore, at 4.30 pm. 				 																Interface				 																																	An interactive session with writers from Manipur, organised by Srijan and Sahitya Akademi, at Srijans Rooftop, from 6 pm to 8 pm. Participants: A.K. Sharma, I.S. Kangjam, K. Prakash Singh, M. Priyabrata, Y. Iboamcha Singh. Anchor: Nabaneeta Dev Sen. 				 																On stage				 																																	Plays on AIDS awareness, Aparadh and Proti Chhoye Second, directed by Sohag Sen and presented by Ensemble at Madhusudan Manch, at 6.30 pm.				 																																	Atmaja, by Gobardanga Naksha, will be staged at Bharatiyam, at 6.30 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	Paintings and sculptures on display at CIMA Gallery, from 2 pm to 7 pm.
